-- THE ONE data file: every row of research for all 107 companies.
--
-- HOW IT WORKS (read this once, it matters):
--   Step 1 of this file WIPES all existing rows from the data tables.
--   Step 2 rebuilds everything from scratch: 107 companies, all metrics,
--          value chains, real-time tags, bull/bear cases, management
--          profiles, market caps and cross-company narratives.
--
-- WHY WIPE FIRST? Because it makes this file impossible to mess up:
--   * Database currently has the old 58 companies?  -> ends with 107.
--   * Database has 58 + a few batches you ran before? -> ends with 107.
--   * You accidentally run this file TWICE?           -> still exactly 107.
--   No duplicate-key errors. No "which batch did I already run?" anxiety.
--   One file, one run, one guaranteed end state.
--
-- IS WIPING SAFE? Yes, in this specific database: every row it deletes is
-- recreated by this same file seconds later. Nothing user-generated lives
-- in these tables, and the robot's staging table is empty by design.
--
-- PREREQUISITE: run 1_SCHEMA_complete.sql first (it is safe to re-run).
-- Generated: 2026-07-03
-- ============================================================================

