INSERT INTO companies (ticker,name,exchange,sector,sub_sector,compare_group,business_core,source_note,moat_note,value_chain_position,value_chain_note) VALUES ('HDFCBANK','HDFC Bank','NSE','Banking','Private Bank','Banks','HDFC Bank takes public deposits and lends the money back out across home loans, vehicle loans, credit cards, SME and corporate credit. It earns mainly on the spread between what it pays depositors and what it charges borrowers (net interest margin), plus fees from cards, insurance distribution and transaction banking. It absorbed parent HDFC Ltd, India''s largest mortgage lender, in a July 2023 merger.','HDFC Bank Q3 FY26 results filing (SEC Form 6-K) and Q4 FY26 investor presentation','Scale + branch network (9,455+ branches) + brand trust. India''s largest private bank by assets and one of three systemically important banks.','No physical value chain — banks face a platform disintermediation dynamic instead. HDFC Bank holds the customer''s account and the underlying money, but the customer-facing ''app layer'' for everyday payments increasingly belongs to someone else.','BIS research on UPI confirms this directly: banks hold a small share of the UPI transaction-initiation market by value, even as the dominant non-bank apps (Google Pay, PhonePe) capture the customer relationship at the point of use.');
